column12: North Dakota Legislative District Caucuses were held Jan. 1 - March 1

column13: Still one preinct shy according to AP. We may never know the true number

column12: Democratic: http://utahdemocrats.org/caucus2016results/, Republican: the Utah Republican Party provided a press release stating "over 200,000" people participated in their caucus

column13: I hate caucuses, this is all I've got for turnout, a tweet from the Washington Democratic Party's communications director
Democrats held a non-binding primary on 5/10. The overall turnout rate excludes this primary and includes the binding Democratic caucus on 3/5

I count all minor party and no party affilated in "Minor" category. There were 107,699 no party affilated and 47,554 minor party votes cast. These are not include in the total ballots cast or turnout rate calculations since none of these voters selected delegates to their party conventions
Not certified results, still some votes outstanding, provisional ballots to be counted
